ia Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred ferch Ieuan was born in 1450. She married Dafydd \"Llwyd\" ap Ieuan in 1465, in Llandyssiliogogo, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 3 daughters. She died in 1530, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1450–1530":"1450–1530","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1465–1548":"1465–1548","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1471–Male":"1471–Surnud","1472–Male":"1472–Surnud","1472–Female":"1472–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","about 1470":"umbes 1470","Abt 1130":"umbes 1130","1465":"1465","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1472":"1472","1471":"1471","1470":"1470","about 1471":"umbes 1471","about 1472":"umbes 1472","1548":"1548","Castell Hywel, Llandyssiliogogo, Cardigan, Wales":"Llandyssiliogogo, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Tal-y-llyn, Merionethshire, Wales":"Tal-y-llyn, Merionethshire, Wales","of Ceiswyn,Tal-y-llyn,Merionethshire,Wales":"Tal-y-llyn, Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1450–1530":"1450–1